%h1 Progresses
%p
  %b 
    By default: option attributes passed into the :progress component are
    %span.text-danger applied to the .progress > .progress-bar div. 

.bg-warning.p-4
  %h4 
    %i Note: Not quite working yet
  %p If you want to adjust the html of the wrapping .progress div, pass in a <b>wrapper_html</b> hash. These will be non-destrutively combined with the default html attributes of the wrapping / parent .progress div. Example:
  %code
    \= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 20, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4', data: { describe: 'a nested data attribute' } }

  %p Will output:

  %p
    %b Component:
  = ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 20, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4', data: { describe: 'a nested data attribute' } }

  %p
    %b HTML

  %code
    = "<div class='progress my-4' data-describe='a nested data attribute'>"
    %br
    %span.ml-4= "<div aria-valuemax='100' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuenow='20' class='progress-bar bg-primary' role='progressbar' style='width: 20%;'></div>"
    %br
    = "</div>"

%hr


%h2 Default progress bars

%p No attributes
= ui.bootstrap :progress

%hr

%h2 Progress
%p 
  Pass in the progress attribute as an integer.
  %br
  %code
    \= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 25

= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 25, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 50, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 75, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 90, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 100, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }

%hr

%h2 Labels

%p Labels can be applied in 3 flavors
%ol
  %li 
    As a boolean (true) on the label attribute which will output the '[:progress]%'
    %br
    %code = ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 25, label: true
    %br
    %b Label will output 25%
  %li
    As a string
    %br
    %code = ui.bootstrap :progress, label: 'My label'
  %li
    As a block
    %br
    %code 
      \= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 30 do
      %br
      %span.ml-4 My custom block label

= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 60, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, label: true
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 75, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, label: 'Custom string'
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 90, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' } do
  Label as a block

%hr

%h2 Height
%p leaving the :height option out will use the default heigh value from CSS
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 60, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, height: 1
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 60, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 60, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, height: 100

%hr

%h2 Themes (backgrounds)
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 15, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, theme: :primary, label: 'Primary'
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 25, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, theme: :secondary, label: 'Secondary'
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 50, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, theme: :success, label: 'Success'
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 75, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, theme: :warning, label: 'Warning'
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 80, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, theme: :danger, label: 'Danger'
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 90, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, theme: :dark, label: 'Dark'
= ui.bootstrap :progress, progress: 95, wrapper_html: { class: 'my-4' }, theme: :light do
  %span.text-dark Light

%hr

%h2.text-danger Multiple bars (not yet supported)

